# Task Runner — just

Every project must have a `justfile` at the repo root. All runnable tasks go here — no raw `make`, `npm run`, or `python -m` commands in docs or CI without a `just` wrapper.

## Default target — help

`help` is always the default target. Running `just` with no arguments lists all available targets.

```justfile
# Show available commands (default)
default:
    @just --list
```

## Standard targets

Every project includes these targets. Add project-specific ones below the standard set.

```justfile
# Show available commands (default)
default:
    @just --list

# Install / bootstrap the project
install:
    pip install -e ".[dev]"

# Run all linting
lint:
    ruff check .

# Auto-fix lint + format
fix:
    ruff check --fix .
    ruff format .

# Type checking
typecheck:
    ty check .

# Run unit tests
test:
    pytest tests/unit

# Run all tests
test-all:
    pytest tests/

# Run a specific test file or pattern (usage: just test-one tests/unit/test_auth.py)
test-one file:
    pytest {{ file }} -v

# Build docker image
build:
    docker build -t {{APP_NAME}} .

# Start local environment
up:
    docker compose up -d

# Stop local environment
down:
    docker compose down

# Full CI check (lint + typecheck + test)
ci:
    just lint && just typecheck && just test-all
```

## Standard targets — JavaScript / TypeScript (bun + vinext)

```justfile
# Show available commands (default)
default:
    @just --list

# Install dependencies
install:
    bun install

# Start development server
dev:
    vinext dev

# Production build
build:
    vinext build

# Deploy to Cloudflare Workers
deploy:
    vinext deploy

# Type check
typecheck:
    bun run tsc --noEmit

# Lint
lint:
    bun run eslint .

# Run tests
test:
    bun test

# Full CI check
ci:
    just typecheck && just lint && just test && just build
```

## Rules

- `just` with no args must always print available targets — never error or run code silently.
- Targets are lowercase, hyphen-separated: `test-all`, not `testAll` or `test_all`.
- Each target has a comment (`# description`) — it appears in `just --list` output.
- Variables (e.g., `APP_NAME`) defined at the top of the justfile or passed as env vars.
- CI pipelines call `just <target>`, never the raw command directly.
- JS/TS projects: use `bun` commands; never `npm run` or `npx` in justfile targets.
